### Question 5 (10 points)

Consider the player Jim Thome (playerID="thomeji01"). For each of
Thome's seasons, give the probability (using the optimal parameter
estimates from Question 3) that he was an elite home run hitter in that
season.

```{r}
thome_data <- subset(Batting.restricted, playerID == "thomeji01")
thome_HRrate <- thome_data$HR / thome_data$AB

